Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.19,0:00:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s theme is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.26,0:00:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“You Are Precious to Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.06,0:00:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some highlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re going through difficult times,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.73,0:00:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,does Jehovah notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.73,0:00:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ll learn in Malu’s experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does care\Nand he helps us overcome
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.11,0:00:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,even the most challenging circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.64,0:00:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer is a powerful way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.64,0:00:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can ask for and receive\Nloving comfort from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that in our new music video.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.28,0:00:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, all over the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses will be inviting people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to this year’s conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Can attending a convention\Nchange a person’s life?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll find out in this report.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.10,0:00:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the April 2020 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.53,0:00:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting®!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.49,0:01:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with the experience\Nof Juan Pablo Zermeño.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how he found a life\Nof real meaning and purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re little,\Nyou just want to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.35,0:01:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But sadly, my father\Nhad a problem with alcohol,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and no child wants to live through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.76,0:01:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, my family\Nfrom the United States came to visit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.43,0:02:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.94,0:02:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The way they talked,\Nit was as though they only had fun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—a good life\Nwith no economic problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.65,0:02:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked myself, ‘How can we live
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.45,0:02:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in such poverty\Nwhile their life is so great?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the life I wanted for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.13,0:02:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I was nine years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.74,0:02:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I left my mother and the rest of my family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to cross the border into the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.58,0:02:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in a pretty rough neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I joined a local gym\Nto learn how to defend myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.66,0:02:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The trainer, Leo, was like a father to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He always tried to give us good advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond was part of the boxing team.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We got along really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.27,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He respected me, and he looked after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After several years of being around Raymond
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.71,0:03:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other members of the team,\NI felt really comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To some extent, I admired him
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.52,0:03:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because I could see\Nthat he was really doing well,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.69,0:03:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because Raymond was selling drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.63,0:03:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that it wasn’t right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.09,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to sell drugs as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.40,0:03:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond was in a drug deal gone wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.38,0:03:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to myself,\N‘This could happen to me too.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It had been six years\Nsince I had seen my mom and my siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.13,0:04:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was studying the Bible\Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It helped her to cope\Nwith a lot of suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.74,0:04:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It brought her peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She was so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to realize\Nthat this was what I really needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I also thought about my friends at the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.38,0:04:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted them to understand why life\Nwas so hard for all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.19,0:04:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so I returned to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.93,0:04:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But they weren’t interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My trainer, Leo, told me\Nthat I didn’t need to sell drugs anymore;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.83,0:04:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he could make me a professional boxer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could help out my family in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He even gave me the nickname The Bible Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.35,0:05:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But I realized that\Nthat was just a temporary solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.29,0:05:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What I was learning\Nwas going to help me forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was determined to serve Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.13,0:05:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I returned to Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to study the Bible\Nand take it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to view Jehovah as my Father
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.64,0:05:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because he helped me\Nto find real relief from my pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to have peace\N—a tranquility that makes you 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.58,0:05:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,feel accepted, loved, and wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.82,0:05:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have enjoyed\Nan incredible life serving Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.76,0:05:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Decades later, my father was baptized\Nas one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has been so kind to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.67,0:05:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,my family, and my siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, I have no way to repay Jehovah\Nfor the life he’s given me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had so many blessings in my life:\Na wonderful wife
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.85,0:06:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and great friends, 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.68,0:06:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,including those that I serve
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,alongside of in Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.59,0:06:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not on my own anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has given me\Na life full of real meaning, purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.79,0:06:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and so much happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.96,0:06:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine\Nleaving your home at the age of nine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Juan Pablo sought a better life,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.50,0:06:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but that only led\Nto danger and disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.31,0:06:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Juan Pablo said that it was\NJehovah who gave him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“a life full of real meaning,\Npurpose, and . . . happiness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Juan Pablo is precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As we mentioned—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme for this month’s program is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.12,0:06:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“You Are Precious to Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.69,0:06:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How vital it is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.23,0:06:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that we remind ourselves of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider three reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Satan wants us to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah doesn’t love us\Nor value our service.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted Job to believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was a lie in Job’s day,\Nand it’s still a lie today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A second reason that we need\Nto be reminded that we’re precious to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of negative circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or events that have taken place in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.10,0:07:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Severe illness,\Nadvancing years, injustices,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.60,0:07:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,mistreatment,\Na difficult family life, or other situations
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,may cause some brothers and sisters\Nto feel that they’re just not worth loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.08,0:07:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Some may question why Jehovah\Nallows those things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.08,0:07:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we need reminders\Nof how Jehovah feels about us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because our imperfection\Ncan cause us to have negative thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:07:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Some may still punish\Nthemselves for past mistakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.93,0:08:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,doubting that Jehovah has forgiven them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.53,0:08:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he could ever love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Others wage a constant battle\Nagainst feelings of worthlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One Witness wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.71,0:08:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Satan has done an excellent job of making
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.44,0:08:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“even those who love Jehovah\Nfeel worthless and unlovable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.25,0:08:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . I never felt worthy of Jehovah’s love,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“so I tried to do\Nmore and more in his service
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.89,0:08:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“as a way of earning that love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.26,0:08:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . So no matter\Nhow many hours I spent in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.39,0:08:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“or how many people I helped,\NI felt it was not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.46,0:08:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw only the lack in me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,One brother stated:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.17,0:08:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“I came from a family\Nthat showed little love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was belittled, teased, and laughed at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.41,0:08:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“So, early in life I felt worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.38,0:08:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“I still carry\Nentrenched feelings from my past
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“that beat me down\Nwhen I experience calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.46,0:09:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I stopped serving\Nas a congregation elder,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.46,0:09:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“I felt like a failure as usual
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—to God, my family,\Nand my brothers in the congregation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.70,0:09:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’ve experienced such feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.14,0:09:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.17,0:09:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you\Nbe assured of Jehovah’s interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s examine three lines of evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.55,0:09:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that prove you’re precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.45,0:09:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we’ll examine\NJehovah’s feelings for the nation of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we’ll reflect\Non an event recorded in the Gospels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And third,\Nwe’ll consider a modern-day example
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of one who was very precious to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.03,0:09:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of the 16th century B.C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.00,0:09:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of Israelites\Nwere enslaved in Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,where they were severely oppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.68,0:09:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In their distress,\Nthe Israelites cried out to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:09:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.15,0:10:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn with me to Isaiah 63:9.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.42,0:10:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}A{\r} portion reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.86,0:10:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“During all their distress
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it was distressing to him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.46,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did Jehovah see their troubles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but he felt for his people,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.27,0:10:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was moved to act in their behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.64,0:10:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 63:9 goes on to say:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.71,0:10:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“In his love and compassion\Nhe repurchased them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah couldn’t see\Ntheir suffering or hear their outcries
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,without feeling for them\Nand doing something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That may remind us of the loving concern
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that a mother has for her newborn child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When that baby cries,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother takes notice
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and she feels for her child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, notice how\Nthis is expressed at Isaiah 49:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.37,0:10:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.37,0:11:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Can a woman forget her nursing child
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.88,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“or have no compassion\Nfor the son of her womb?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even if these women forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never forget you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s hard to imagine a mother forgetting\Nto nourish and care for her nursing child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.16,0:11:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That baby is helpless
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.20,0:11:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—day and night\Nit needs its mother’s attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.97,0:11:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sad to say, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.97,0:11:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that we hear at times\Nof such maternal neglect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did Jehovah say\Nto reassure the Israelites?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.38,0:11:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“I would never forget you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.28,0:11:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the tender compassion\Nthat Jehovah felt for his servants
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.68,0:11:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was immeasurably stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,than one of the most tender\Nand natural feelings we can imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.12,0:11:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—the compassion\Na mother normally feels for her baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s feelings for the Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are summed up\Nin another expression in the book of Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.63,0:12:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please read with me Isaiah 43:4:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“For you became precious in my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.61,0:12:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you were honored, and I have loved you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah clearly expressed\Nhis feelings for his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As one of Jehovah’s servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be sure\Nthat he also loves you most tenderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what trials you’re facing now\Nor have endured in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.63,0:12:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sees you and he feels for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.30,0:12:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hurt, he hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.67,0:12:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re far too precious to Jehovah\Nfor him to forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.48,0:12:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He remembers your past efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.78,0:12:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sees\Nyour continuing efforts to please him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how Jehovah promises\Nto sustain and comfort his people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Isaiah 66:12, 13:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will nurse and be carried on the hip,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you will be bounced on the knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.10,0:13:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“As a mother comforts her son,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.40,0:13:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so I will keep comforting you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What a heartwarming scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a loving mother\Ncarrying a baby on her hip
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.18,0:13:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or bouncing him on her knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.15,0:13:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah touchingly illustrates the intensity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.02,0:13:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and tenderness of his love for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.76,0:13:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Jehovah loved his people, Israel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he likewise feels that you\Nare very precious and dear
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.53,0:13:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—never doubt that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.13,0:13:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A second example\Nof how Jehovah feels
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about his faithful servants\Ncan be found in the Gospels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read what happened on one occasion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.61,0:13:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus was at the temple in Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at Luke 21:1-4:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.28,0:13:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now as he looked up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“he saw the rich dropping their gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.79,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“into the treasury chests.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he saw a needy widow drop in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.26,0:14:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“two small coins of very little value,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.23,0:14:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Truly I say to you that this poor widow
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.43,0:14:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘put in more than they all did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.94,0:14:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For all of these put in gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘out of their surplus,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.97,0:14:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘but she, out of her want
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.44,0:14:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘[or as the footnote says, “poverty”],
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,put in all the means of living she had.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The study note for verse 2
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.32,0:14:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}of the Holy Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us that the Greek word\Nfor “needy” may describe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.49,0:14:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“a person who lacks\Nthe basic necessities of life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“or someone for whom\Nlife is a great struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Christian Greek Scriptures,\Nit is used only here.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.41,0:14:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think about the widow’s circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.58,0:14:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only had she experienced the grief
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.88,0:14:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of losing her husband, her provider,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.61,0:15:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but she also lived in a religious climate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.15,0:15:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,dominated by leaders who,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Luke 20:47,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,would “devour the houses of the widows”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.19,0:15:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than help such vulnerable ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.73,0:15:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That widow was so poor\Nthat her contribution to the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.13,0:15:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was what a laborer\Nmight earn in just a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.70,0:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Life wasn’t easy for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jesus said that she
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.74,0:15:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“put in all the means of living she had.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.25,0:15:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Our publications have stated\Nthat the coins the widow contributed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.38,0:15:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,were likely two lepta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,With eight lepta,\Na person could buy two sparrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which were among the cheapest birds\Nused for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.19,0:15:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the widow had\Nonly half the amount needed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.73,0:15:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy one sparrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.17,0:15:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,hardly enough for a single meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, both the widow and her contribution
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.11,0:15:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,were valuable to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.97,0:16:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that her contribution was greater
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,than the contributions of the rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.01,0:16:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When she put those two small coins\Nin the treasury chest,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.02,0:16:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they would be mixed\Nwith what the rich had put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.52,0:16:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To imperfect human eyes,\Nthey might seem lost, buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.43,0:16:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, this precious widow\Nwas the one Jesus singled out for praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.56,0:16:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When the treasury workers\Ncame across the coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.63,0:16:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn’t have known\Nhow precious the coins and their donor
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,were to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But God’s view\Nwas the one that really mattered,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,not what other people thought
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or even how that dear widow viewed herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like that widow,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.88,0:16:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you may find that circumstances limit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what you can contribute to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Age, infirmities,\Nor other circumstances beyond your control
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:16:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,may limit the amount of time\Nyou’re able to spend in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:16:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You might feel\Nthat your efforts are like those
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.27,0:17:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“two small coins of very little value.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we learn from this account\Nof the needy widow
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.57,0:17:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah notices\Nand he treasures each act done for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.58,0:17:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when we do it\Ndespite difficult circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.85,0:17:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For a moment, think back on your worship\Nof Jehovah during the past year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.56,0:17:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you may feel\Nthat you accomplished little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your imperfect heart\Nmight cause you to wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.46,0:17:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whether Jehovah\Nwas pleased with your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, did one of the hours you spent
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.04,0:17:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,require a special sacrifice on your part?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.14,0:17:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah took notice of the widow
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.51,0:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dropping in those two coins\Nand valued her contribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.28,0:17:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you think he also noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.45,0:17:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and valued what you did\Nfor him during that hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.69,0:17:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah values every gift,\Nno matter how small,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that springs from a heart motivated by love.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He remembers, and he’ll reward
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.50,0:18:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,even the smallest contribution\Ngiven in support of his Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.07,0:18:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s proof of how Jehovah feels about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, let’s consider a modern-day example
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.44,0:18:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of one who was very precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the experience of Sister Areti Pina.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pina lived\Non the southern coast of Albania
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the town of Vlorë.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.82,0:18:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She was baptized in 1928 at the age of 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a strong congregation \Nin Vlorë in the 1930’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.93,0:18:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sister Pina was a zealous evangelizer
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.87,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who climbed up and down rugged mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,preaching with her Bible in hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.54,0:18:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, a congregation\Nno longer existed in Vlorë,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.28,0:18:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sister Pina lost contact\Nwith the brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.78,0:18:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, she kept preaching faithfully\Non her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.68,0:18:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think her efforts\Nwent unnoticed by Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.09,0:19:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, years later, word reached the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an old, senile woman
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.53,0:19:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who was reportedly preaching in Vlorë.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.63,0:19:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People thought she was crazy\Nfor keeping faith in God
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.80,0:19:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,during years of totalitarian rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.97,0:19:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Sister Pina, now in her 80’s,\Nwas anything but senile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.81,0:19:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When the brothers arrived at her home,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.14,0:19:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pina invited them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.48,0:19:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but she seemed somewhat reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.38,0:19:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When they explained\Nthat they were her spiritual brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.42,0:19:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,she had no reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.32,0:19:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,After a few minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pina started firing\Nquestions at the brothers:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.66,0:19:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you believe in the Trinity?\NWhat is God’s name?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.13,0:19:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you believe in hellfire?\NWhat happens when we die?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.77,0:19:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the earth?\NHow many go to heaven?”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.37,0:19:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers answered each question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you preach?” she then asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.94,0:19:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Yes,” said one brother, “we preach.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.95,0:20:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“But,” she responded, \N“how do you preach?”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.35,0:20:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“We preach from house to house,”\Nreplied the brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.52,0:20:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now I know that you are my brothers!”\Nshe exclaimed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.66,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only Jehovah’s people\Npreach from house to house!”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Through her tears, Sister Pina stated:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.33,0:20:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is wonderful.\NHe never forgot me!”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.51,0:20:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime later, the brothers\Nwere notified that Sister Pina was ill
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and that she wanted to meet\Nwith one of the responsible brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.78,0:20:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When he arrived, she asked in part,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as she gasped for air,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.22,0:20:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Has the book of Revelation been fulfilled?”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.89,0:20:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The brother responded,\N“Yes, Areti, most of it has.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.89,0:20:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pina said:\N“Now I can die in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.53,0:20:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to know how close we are.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after that conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:21:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Pina\Nfaithfully finished her earthly course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.75,0:21:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,During all those years of isolation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.18,0:21:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from the earthly part\Nof Jehovah’s organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.88,0:21:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,did Sister Pina’s efforts\Ngo unnoticed by Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.29,0:21:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine Jehovah’s joy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.93,0:21:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as he watched her faithfully doing\Nwhat she could in his service.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that Sister Pina\Nwas precious to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.67,0:21:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.14,0:21:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your efforts in Jehovah’s service\Ndo not go unnoticed by him either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.01,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Sister Pina, you are precious to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.88,0:21:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what has this consideration\Nhelped us to realize?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.82,0:21:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We may have to contend with Satan’s lies,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.56,0:21:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,negative circumstances\Nand events in our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and our own imperfections.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.03,0:21:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should never forget\Nthat Jehovah highly values his servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.93,0:22:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw that in his words to the Israelites\Nthrough the prophet Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.27,0:22:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be sure that Jehovah\Nloves you most tenderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.21,0:22:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what trials you’re facing now\Nor have endured in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.55,0:22:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sees you and he feels for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.12,0:22:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hurt, he hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re far too precious to Jehovah\Nfor him to forget you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.56,0:22:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The account of the widow in Luke chapter 21
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.16,0:22:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,can assure you that although circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,may affect what you\Ncan contribute to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.50,0:22:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he notices and treasures\Neach act you do for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.07,0:22:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when you do it\Nin the face of difficult circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.68,0:22:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He remembers,\Nand he will reward
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.31,0:22:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,even the smallest contribution\Ngiven in support of his Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.72,0:22:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And what beautiful modern-day examples\Nwe have in the organization
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.89,0:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of brothers and sisters\Nwho have proven their loyalty to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and are precious to him,\Nlike the example of Sister Pina!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.40,0:23:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear brothers and sisters, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.94,0:23:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,never forget that you\Nare precious to Jehovah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s another modern-day example
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—Sister Malu Mørch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.28,0:23:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ll see, she faced a number
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.18,0:23:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of serious hardships early in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.12,0:23:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice all the ways\Nshe received comfort from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.53,0:23:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Malu Mørch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.70,0:23:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.24,0:23:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how much Jehovah has helped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.75,0:23:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised in Sisimiut in Greenland.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.92,0:23:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My childhood was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.35,0:24:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very often out in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.42,0:24:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In the summer, we sailed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.42,0:24:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the winter, we rode dog sledge
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.53,0:24:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and we went hunting and fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.43,0:24:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a child,\NI was very close to my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.17,0:24:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a “daddy’s girl.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.20,0:24:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He called me “My Beloved,”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.40,0:24:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so “Beloved” became my nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.44,0:24:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been so wonderful\Nto be raised in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.31,0:24:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest gift that I could get
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.81,0:24:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is to know Jehovah through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.52,0:24:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was nine years old,\Nmy parents got divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.03,0:24:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw how my siblings were hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.36,0:24:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot be explained how—\NI mean, we were very wounded in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.37,0:24:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When my parents divorced,\Nmy father was disfellowshipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very hard to be separated like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.87,0:24:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I missed my dad a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.81,0:24:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When my mom started to drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.78,0:24:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I also felt abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.65,0:25:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I knew what she had been doing,\NI was not surprised when, 
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.49,0:25:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,after some time, she was disfellowshipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.49,0:25:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, I felt very hurt and sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.49,0:25:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I supplicated Jehovah\Nto help me stay in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.97,0:25:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The pioneer sister who studied\Nwith me helped me a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.64,0:25:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She studied with me and sometimes took me
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.31,0:25:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry and invited me to dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.71,0:25:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was about 12 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.75,0:25:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,my father came back into the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.38,0:25:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very happy that it finally happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.76,0:25:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to have\Na good relationship with him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.76,0:25:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We sailed a lot,\Ndrove snowmobiles, and rode dog sledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.03,0:25:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and my father and I\Nwatched movies in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.63,0:25:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that when my dad\Nheard that I was going to be baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.84,0:25:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he shed a tear,\Nand I could see that he was proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.95,0:26:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 15 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.69,0:26:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,my world fell to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.12,0:26:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My father committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.43,0:26:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s difficult to describe\Nthat my father was suddenly gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.77,0:26:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t understand
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.80,0:26:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,why he would do such a selfish thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.24,0:26:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I missed him a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.21,0:26:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like my heart was stabbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.62,0:26:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also very angry at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.43,0:26:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.66,0:26:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wrote many letters to my father
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.17,0:27:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about things that I wanted to tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.27,0:27:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I also cried out to Jehovah in long prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.84,0:27:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Psalm 34:18
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.68,0:27:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah being close\Nto “those who are crushed in spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.01,0:27:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That was how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.35,0:27:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thought that Jehovah is close to them
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.25,0:27:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,comforts me a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.29,0:27:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I also did all I could\Nto go to all the meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.69,0:27:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,even when I didn’t want to see anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.33,0:27:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I had cried before the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.53,0:27:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I went anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.67,0:27:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One month after my father’s death,\NI got baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.01,0:27:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized because I loved Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.98,0:27:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was nine years old,\NI had promised Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.65,0:27:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve him for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.49,0:27:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My relationship with my mother\Nis much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.99,0:28:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is great to serve Jehovah\Ntogether with her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.36,0:28:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We preach together every Sunday,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.67,0:28:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I always look forward to going\Nin the ministry together with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.74,0:28:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 18 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.04,0:28:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to help\Nin the remote translation office.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.98,0:28:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, I started pioneering.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.92,0:28:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always learned a lot from King David.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.02,0:28:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what circumstances he faced,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.59,0:28:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,whether bad or good,\Nhe used them to draw close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.46,0:28:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has helped me to overcome 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.47,0:28:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,challenges through the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.10,0:28:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,giving me “power beyond what is normal”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.44,0:28:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and taking me in as his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.61,0:28:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As a child,\NMalu’s nickname was Beloved.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.28,0:28:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, for a while,\Nshe felt anything but loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.89,0:29:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She said that her “world fell to pieces.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.26,0:29:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.26,0:29:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what helped\NMalu stay close to Jehovah:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.10,0:29:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A pioneer sister encouraged her;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.73,0:29:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,personal study reminded Malu
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.94,0:29:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah helped his servants in the past;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.87,0:29:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,she pursued spiritual goals,\Nsuch as auxiliary pioneering;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.04,0:29:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and she went\Nto as many Christian meetings as she could,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.48,0:29:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even when she wanted to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.32,0:29:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In all these ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.32,0:29:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Malu was reminded\Nthat she is precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.25,0:29:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As she said,\N‘Jehovah has taken me in as his daughter.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.43,0:29:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For some people, staying busy\Nmay seem like the right thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.43,0:29:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when they’ve suffered a serious setback.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.13,0:29:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Does staying busy really help?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.84,0:29:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s find out in this dramatization.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.18,0:29:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Steven, take you, Emily,\Nto be my wedded wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.95,0:30:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Emily, take you, Steven,\Nto be my wedded husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.06,0:30:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no doubt our vows were forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.43,0:30:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing could have prepared me\Nfor the heartbreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.90,0:30:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I never expected her to be unfaithful
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.77,0:30:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and unwilling to work things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.49,0:30:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt humiliated.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.09,0:30:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How could she do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.83,0:30:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was embarrassed,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.83,0:30:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t want to talk to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.94,0:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I read somewhere that time\Nwould help me heal
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.98,0:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and just to stay busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.22,0:31:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.89,0:31:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was constantly reminded of what I lost:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.19,0:31:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual goals,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.76,0:31:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the hopes and dreams we had
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.90,0:31:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—all destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.74,0:31:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to dwell on the hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.74,0:31:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just couldn’t ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.29,0:31:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Was I really coping?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.33,0:31:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was I leaving myself open\Nto even more pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.90,0:32:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters,\Nwe’re going to talk about marriage today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.64,0:32:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If we turn to Ephesians chapter 5, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.20,0:32:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was angry, but not just with Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.81,0:32:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was angry with everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.71,0:32:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven!\NSteven!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.85,0:32:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let me stop by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.96,0:32:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What I had to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.30,0:32:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t have blamed Tom for judging me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.30,0:32:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but he didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.20,0:32:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right, Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.80,0:32:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.81,0:32:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know who can.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.21,0:32:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember Psalm 34?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.48,0:32:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think verse 18 says it best.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.15,0:32:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you read it for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.02,0:33:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is close to the brokenhearted;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.23,0:33:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he saves those who are crushed in spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.77,0:33:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful scripture?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.03,0:33:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Take advantage of Jehovah\Nbeing that close to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.61,0:33:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and include him in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.34,0:33:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}is {\r} a loving Shepherd.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.05,0:33:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When we hurt, he cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.08,0:33:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew this, but in a way, I’d forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.09,0:33:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I hadn’t included Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.79,0:33:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ways I tried to cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.16,0:33:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying busy was important,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.36,0:33:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but I needed to draw closer to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.66,0:33:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not push away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.83,0:33:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.84,0:33:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the real healing began.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.41,0:33:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the pain is still there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.61,0:33:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sees the tears;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.08,0:33:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah feels what I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.42,0:34:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is getting better, slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.43,0:34:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because “Jehovah is close\Nto the brokenhearted.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.99,0:34:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The vast majority of marriages\Namong Jehovah’s people prosper
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.16,0:34:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because Christian husbands and wives
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.16,0:34:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,apply Bible principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.56,0:34:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but a few fail to live up\Nto their marriage commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.77,0:34:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you among the brokenhearted?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.71,0:34:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, never forget\Nthat you are precious to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.68,0:34:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and remember what will help you heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.58,0:35:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In our dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.58,0:35:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven kept himself busy\Nwith recreation and other activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.75,0:35:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But he experienced\Ntrue comfort and healing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.69,0:35:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when he drew close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.96,0:35:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Always remember\Nhow Jehovah is described
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.90,0:35:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 34:18:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.53,0:35:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is close to the brokenhearted;
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.63,0:35:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he saves those who are crushed in spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.37,0:35:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer is one of the most powerful ways
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.87,0:35:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helps us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.88,0:35:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see that in our new music video.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.36,0:35:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When I called yesterday,\NI could tell you’d lost your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.90,0:36:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Be assured you are loved\NBy our God up above.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.88,0:36:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So do not fear.\NWhen you’re broken, he is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.96,0:36:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah; don’t give in.\NJust let it go; roll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.63,0:36:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not alone; you can pray.\NHe hears your words; he feels your pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.98,0:36:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t keep that burden in.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.59,0:36:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Roll it on him.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.89,0:37:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise your eyes up and see;\NThe new world is in our reach—
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.53,0:37:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No more tears, only love\NThrough the gift of God’s dear Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.11,0:37:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But until then,\NWe can endure down to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.52,0:37:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we trust in Jehovah; don’t give in.\NJust let it go; roll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.33,0:37:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not alone; we can pray.\NHe hears our words; he feels our pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.87,0:37:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t keep that burden in.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.15,0:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Roll it on him.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.16,0:38:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah; don’t give in.\NJust let it go; roll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.10,0:38:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not alone; we can pray.\NHe hears our words; he feels our pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.21,0:38:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t keep that burden in.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.58,0:39:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Roll it on him.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.72,0:39:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Roll it on him.\NRoll it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.91,0:39:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful reminder
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.01,0:39:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can go to Jehovah\Nin prayer at any time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.81,0:39:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and express our deepest feelings to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.05,0:39:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As the song says:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.05,0:39:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t keep that burden in.\NRoll it on him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.09,0:39:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When we’re experiencing\Npain and difficulty in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.59,0:39:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it may not be easy to see\Nall that Jehovah is doing in our behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.60,0:39:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following Morning Worship program,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.07,0:39:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother John Ekrann helps us\Nto see Jehovah’s hand in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.64,0:39:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, I think all of us would agree
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.64,0:39:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s easy to see Jehovah’s hand
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.87,0:39:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when things are going well
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.88,0:39:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—when we get a court victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.11,0:40:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when someone’s health improves,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.71,0:40:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe when someone really asked to come
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.88,0:40:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the Bible with us\Nand they’re at our meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.49,0:40:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s harder to see Jehovah’s hand\Nwhen we see bad things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.39,0:40:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,either to us or to our brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.86,0:40:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we may wonder,\N‘How can we see Jehovah’s hand
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.10,0:40:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when bad things are happening?’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.60,0:40:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can see my hand right now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.41,0:40:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I put it away, you can’t see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.68,0:40:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, do you assume\Nthat because you can’t see my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.21,0:40:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that I don’t have a hand anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.22,0:40:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.58,0:40:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You reason on the fact\Nthat since you see the rest of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.59,0:40:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s probably still my hand attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.86,0:40:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So likewise, there are times\Nwhen it’s easy to see Jehovah’s hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.76,0:40:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are other times\Nwhen we have to reason
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.83,0:40:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on what we know about Jehovah\Nin order to see his hand in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.77,0:40:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s consider one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.77,0:40:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we know about Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.77,0:41:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could reason\Nthat his hand is in action?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.14,0:41:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s reason on the point\Nthat he is a “happy God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.95,0:41:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how does Jehovah stay happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.19,0:41:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing all the bad things that are happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.85,0:41:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’ve wondered that.\NI know it’s crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.72,0:41:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Jehovah stay happy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.33,0:41:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when he sees\Nall the suffering that’s going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.60,0:41:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, he sees {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}all {\r} the suffering;
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.67,0:41:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he sees everything going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.67,0:41:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how I feel,\Nand you probably know how you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.54,0:41:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,just when you read about what’s happening
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.87,0:41:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to our brothers in Venezuela or in Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.51,0:41:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or with all of the hurricanes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.55,0:41:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and earthquakes\Nthat we’ve had in recent times.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.51,0:41:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not only of our brothers and sisters\Nbut also of other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.02,0:41:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we consider,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.02,0:41:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How can Jehovah stay happy\Nwhen he knows all of what is happening?’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.99,0:41:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider three\N(I’m sure) of many reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.83,0:41:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,why Jehovah can stay happy\Neven though he knows all the suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.97,0:42:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we can see\Nhow that could benefit us as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.97,0:42:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.97,0:42:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,his hand is hard at work\Npreparing the new world for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.11,0:42:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think Jeremiah 29:11
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.68,0:42:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,really covers how Jehovah feels
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.01,0:42:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about the future for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.35,0:42:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,At Jeremiah 29:11, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.99,0:42:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I well know the thoughts\Nthat I am thinking toward you,’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.82,0:42:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares Jehovah,\N‘thoughts of peace, and not of calamity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.93,0:42:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to give you a future and a hope.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.76,0:42:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah\Nis not simply just watching events occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.00,0:42:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s actively working on the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.71,0:42:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He, along with Jesus and the heavenly angels,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.37,0:42:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is working hard on the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.94,0:42:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we can’t see into heaven right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.05,0:42:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want you to just imagine\Nall the activity of the angels,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.05,0:42:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the resurrected anointed brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.19,0:42:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jesus working hard on making preparations
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.79,0:43:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for Armageddon and the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.36,0:43:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think of all the work\Nwe’re doing just to prepare
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.73,0:43:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for the annual meeting and dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.73,0:43:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine all the work\Ngoing on in heaven that is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.57,0:43:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how far along are the new scrolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.74,0:43:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How are our basic needs \Nas far as clean water,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.51,0:43:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,food, and homes\Ngoing to be provided for the survivors?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.01,0:43:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So while we can’t see into heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.92,0:43:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that his hand is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.15,0:43:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah is happy\Nbecause he’s actively working right now
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.52,0:43:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to make things better for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.86,0:43:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the lesson for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.86,0:43:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be happy\Nwhen we see the suffering around us
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.23,0:43:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because we know what Jehovah\Nand our brothers are doing up there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.87,0:43:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare for the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.20,0:43:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A second point about how Jehovah can be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.17,0:43:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is that he can comfort us right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.74,0:43:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He is happy when he can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.08,0:43:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 12 of Jeremiah chapter 29,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.52,0:43:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah continued after saying\Nthat he was working on the future (he says): 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.22,0:44:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you will call me\Nand come and pray to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.99,0:44:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will listen to you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.89,0:44:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I love this point\Nbecause Jehovah is saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.70,0:44:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Don’t worry; I’m taking care\Nof building a better future for you.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.44,0:44:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.74,0:44:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re going through some trial\N—some difficulty—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.94,0:44:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good friend of ours reminds us,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.77,0:44:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember things are going\Nto get better in the future;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.21,0:44:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is going to change this;\Nit’s going to get better,”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.55,0:44:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it is comforting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.21,0:44:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is also comforting \N(like Jehovah says here in verse 12)
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.48,0:44:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when the person says,\N“What can I do for you right now?”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.62,0:44:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is saying right now,\N‘Come, pray to me.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.56,0:44:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is there to comfort and help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.23,0:44:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We could kind of illustrate\Nthe way Jehovah feels
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.06,0:44:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by thinking about parents\Nand how they deal with a small child.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.90,0:44:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen a small child,\Nmaybe two or three years of age,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.57,0:44:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and they fall really badly\Nand scrape their knees badly,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.54,0:44:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are screaming in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.88,0:45:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s this red liquid leaking out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.45,0:45:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They are distraught.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.55,0:45:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in that child’s mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.55,0:45:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he may think: ‘This is the end of it.\NThis is the end of my life as I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.59,0:45:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m never going to recover from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.26,0:45:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to die.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.53,0:45:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But for the parents, of course,\Ntheir perspective is different, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.66,0:45:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But they comfort the child;\Nthey help to take care of the skinned knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.00,0:45:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They comfort them, and they tell them:\N“You’re going to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.10,0:45:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s going to be OK.\NIt’s going to be all right.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.84,0:45:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And why can the parent have that view?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.84,0:45:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they know that in a few hours maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.68,0:45:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,(at least in a week or so),
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.68,0:45:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the child is not even going to remember\Nthat skinned knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.68,0:45:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s going to be just a very distant memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.45,0:45:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah also knows\Nthat whatever we’re going through right now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.99,0:45:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—whatever suffering\Nwe may be going through now—
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.33,0:45:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that soon in that new world,\Nwe aren’t going to recall that suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.13,0:45:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And he knows that he can solve\Nany problem we’re facing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.97,0:45:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as easily as we heal from a scraped knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.14,0:45:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows our whole eternal lives\Nare ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.84,0:46:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So he comforts us;\Nhe listens to our heartfelt prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.11,0:46:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And like a kind parent, he’s telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.41,0:46:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,(through our brothers,\Nthe Bible, and holy spirit),
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.85,0:46:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You will live.’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.39,0:46:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is happy\Nbecause right now, what can he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.89,0:46:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He can comfort us and help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.02,0:46:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is the lesson for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.03,0:46:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can comfort and help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.03,0:46:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re, really, kind of all\Nin this “lifeboat” together,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.90,0:46:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to make it to the “new-world shore,”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.90,0:46:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can help one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.27,0:46:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Third,\Nhis hand is patiently waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.11,0:46:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the right time to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.11,0:46:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is waiting patiently
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.78,0:46:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for the complete vindication\Nof his sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.32,0:46:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I really love\Nwhat the June 2017 {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower {\r} article
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.89,0:46:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep Your Eyes on the Big Issue” said:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.46,0:46:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let us not become\Nso absorbed in our own lives
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.36,0:46:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“that we lose sight of this big issue
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.03,0:46:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“—the vindication of Jehovah’s sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.66,0:47:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“And let us appreciate\Nthat our role in this vital issue
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.00,0:47:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“entails remaining faithful
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.00,0:47:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,even under difficult circumstances.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.74,0:47:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful quote to think about?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.64,0:47:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows that by his being patient now,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.45,0:47:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he and all his faithful servants\Nwill never have to go through this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.38,0:47:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The issue of sovereignty\Nwill be completely settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.12,0:47:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you admire Jehovah’s patience?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.66,0:47:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, to watch all that is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.43,0:47:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and to have the self-control\Nto wait for the appointed time
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.40,0:47:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is truly an example of patience in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.14,0:47:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think about the different situations
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.64,0:47:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters and others face
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.67,0:47:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—when a mother, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.68,0:47:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,watches a handicapped son\Nstruggle to walk or to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.25,0:47:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or a husband watches his wife\Nstruggle to breathe—
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.32,0:47:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we want so much at that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.65,0:47:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to press that big, red,\N“start-the-new-world” button now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.72,0:48:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you have that feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.26,0:48:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,remember our text for today:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.46,0:48:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“The hand of Jehovah\Nwill become known to his servants.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.80,0:48:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the lesson for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.81,0:48:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be patient
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.81,0:48:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep our eyes\Non the big issue of Jehovah’s sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.38,0:48:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s just review those three points.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.05,0:48:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we see Jehovah’s hand
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.59,0:48:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and be happy when we see\Nall of this suffering around us?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.29,0:48:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can be happy knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.29,0:48:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what Jehovah and Jesus\Nand the resurrected anointed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.43,0:48:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,are doing right now\Nto prepare for the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.36,0:48:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be happy\Nbecause we have a role
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.07,0:48:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in comforting and helping others.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.87,0:48:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can be happy being patient,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.61,0:48:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing why we’re being patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.74,0:48:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have our eyes\Non that big issue of Jehovah’s sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.05,0:48:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not always\Nbe able to see Jehovah’s hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.55,0:49:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can be sure,\Nas our text for today says,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.09,0:49:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah’s hand is there,\Nand it will become known.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.53,0:49:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, millions of people\Ncome together at our conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn about Jehovah\Nand encourage each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.04,0:49:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting next month,\N“Always Rejoice”! Conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.97,0:49:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will be held all over the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.58,0:49:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nwill be actively inviting their neighbors,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.58,0:49:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,workmates, schoolmates,\Nand all interested ones to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.35,0:49:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What effect can receiving an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.75,0:49:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,have on a person’s life?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.82,0:49:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch the following report.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.36,0:49:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to Greece as an immigrant\Nwhen I was just 16 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.20,0:49:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, I never felt safe
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.40,0:49:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with people around me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.44,0:49:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, I was renting
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.44,0:49:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,an apartment from a man\Nwho was studying the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.28,0:49:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.78,0:50:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,One day I joined the study,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.95,0:50:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brother invited me to the convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.55,0:50:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very cautious at the beginning,\Nbut the brother seemed trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.56,0:50:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I always had questions about the true God,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.30,0:50:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted to learn more about Him,\Nso I decided to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.07,0:50:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.44,0:50:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I received an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.91,0:50:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from my son to attend
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.41,0:50:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the convention of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.41,0:50:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was getting baptized at that convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.68,0:50:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was important to him\Nfor me to be there,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.91,0:50:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and so he asked me to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.95,0:50:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I was very active\Nin another religion for 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.72,0:50:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I went in order to please him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.26,0:50:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned the truth after I supplicated God\Nwith all my strength
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.26,0:50:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was really lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.26,0:50:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked for answers to questions
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.27,0:50:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that were yet unanswered.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.00,0:50:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And God answered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.00,0:51:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave me the answer\Nto my prayers when I found this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.31,0:51:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This invitation, “Deliverance at Hand!,”\Nwas the answer to my prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.78,0:51:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Arriving there, at that convention,\NI observed the crowd—many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.69,0:51:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting right at the parking lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.59,0:51:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,everything was organized;\Npeople were entering in an orderly manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.63,0:51:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside the Assembly Hall,\Neveryone was very organized,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.50,0:51:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,well-dressed, very loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.07,0:51:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the convention began,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.83,0:51:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw such spiritual food\Nthat I had never seen in my religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.57,0:51:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty years in a religion\N—I thought I knew a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.94,0:51:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.91,0:51:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.98,0:51:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived at the convention,\NI started watching the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.19,0:51:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Their faces were smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.22,0:51:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They seemed to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.59,0:51:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There were men, women, and children\Nfrom different races and nationalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.00,0:51:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When they sang,\NI could sense their true joy and unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.67,0:52:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in my life,\NI felt very safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.97,0:52:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not in fear\Nof being taken advantage of.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.65,0:52:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, what I learned at that convention
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.18,0:52:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,drew me to the true God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.85,0:52:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, ‘If all these people
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.89,0:52:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘are truly happy and feel really safe\Nbeing part of this organization
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.29,0:52:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‘—Jehovah’s organization—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.30,0:52:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then, indeed,\Nthis is what I was looking for.’
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.50,0:52:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the convention on Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.87,0:52:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really warmly welcomed\Nby all the brothers and sisters there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.54,0:52:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I listened to all of the morning program,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.21,0:52:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and at noon,\NI recognized the sound of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.98,0:52:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure it was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.95,0:52:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to become\None of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.09,0:52:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I became one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.23,0:53:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized in 2017,\Nand now I serve as a pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.80,0:53:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My first study was the following Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.17,0:53:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was happy to get to know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.90,0:53:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I am one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.74,0:53:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and as much as I can,\NI participate in the invitation campaigns.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.58,0:53:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hope that it helps\Nmany people to be delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.85,0:53:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I started attending meetings\Nright after the convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.02,0:53:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I started a Bible study,\Nand eventually I got baptized
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.99,0:53:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.56,0:53:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother, one of my brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.93,0:53:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and my two sisters\Nare now serving Jehovah as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.20,0:53:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on, I got married to a faithful sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.20,0:53:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a very good wife,\Nand we serve Jehovah together.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.01,0:53:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,People need to feel safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.04,0:53:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know for sure that Jehovah’s\Norganization is the safest place you can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.22,0:54:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how\Nthe convention invitations were obtained?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.22,0:54:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They were given by a relative\Nor an associate
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.36,0:54:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or simply left at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.73,0:54:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We never know how even a single invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.00,0:54:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,can help a person come to know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.30,0:54:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Our diligence in the invitation campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.14,0:54:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,can make a powerful difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.01,0:54:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s program\Nhas helped us remember
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.91,0:54:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.08,0:54:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned that even if we\Nhad a hard start in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.95,0:54:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t have to be a victim of our past.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.69,0:54:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw how Jehovah sees us,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.69,0:54:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,cares for us,\Nand provides loving help in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.09,0:54:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We were reminded\Nthat “Jehovah is close to the brokenhearted”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.43,0:54:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and that through prayer,\Nwe can unburden ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.13,0:54:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and receive comfort,\Nknowing that whatever suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.27,0:54:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re enduring now will soon be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.08,0:54:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s conclude our program by visiting\Nour brothers and sisters in Cuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.51,0:55:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Republic of Cuba\Nis a chain of 1,600 islands and islets
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.25,0:55:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at the intersection of the Atlantic Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.65,0:55:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the Caribbean Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.09,0:55:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Gulf of Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.79,0:55:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Cuba itself is by far\Nthe largest island in the chain,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.43,0:55:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with one major city: Havana.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.73,0:55:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Many are embracing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.00,0:55:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Cuba is home to almost 95,000 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.94,0:55:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1,400 congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.24,0:55:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re conducting\Nmore than 135,000 Bible studies. 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.25,0:55:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lush mountains and hills\Ncover a quarter of Cuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.12,0:55:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At the western end\Nof the island is Viñales,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.02,0:55:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,famous for its towerlike hills\Ncalled {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}mogotes{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.69,0:55:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Caves and rivers run through many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.50,0:55:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Este de Viñales Congregation\Nis located in this part of Cuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.20,0:55:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, 128 publishers conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.54,0:55:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,275 Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.57,0:56:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of its vast territory,\Nthe congregation has three groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.68,0:56:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One group that has only seven publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.38,0:56:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,had 75 people attend last year’s Memorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.25,0:56:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To cover their territory,\Nthe brothers travel long distances,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.69,0:56:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes by bicycle or motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.36,0:56:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They witness to people wherever they are
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.16,0:56:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—on farms and in their homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.97,0:56:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers enjoy Christian fellowship,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.60,0:56:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,good coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.60,0:56:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and singing songs of praise to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.04,0:56:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nin the Este de Viñales Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.08,0:56:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,send their love to the worldwide brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.91,0:56:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.62,0:56:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!
